{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "This PR modifies setup.py and auxiliary files to make Dedalus pip-installable using more modern pip practices. In particular, [MANIFEST.in](http://MANIFEST.in) and pyproject.toml are used to make sure the necessary files are included in a sdist for pip, and that pip grabs the correct build-time requirements \\(e.g. cython\\) before trying to run setup.py.\r\n\r\nIt also adds the flags needed to statically link FFTW with clang on Mac.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This PR modifies setup.py and auxiliary files to make Dedalus pip-installable using more modern pip practices. In particular, <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://MANIFEST.in\" rel=\"nofollow\">MANIFEST.in</a> and pyproject.toml are used to make sure the necessary files are included in a sdist for pip, and that pip grabs the correct build-time requirements (e.g. cython) before trying to run setup.py.</p>\n<p>It also adds the flags needed to statically link FFTW with clang on Mac.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Update for modern pip installation", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Update for modern pip installation</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "This PR modifies setup.py and auxiliary files to make Dedalus pip-installable using more modern pip practices. In particular, [MANIFEST.in](http://MANIFEST.in) and pyproject.toml are used to make sure the necessary files are included in a sdist for pip, and that pip grabs the correct build-time requirements \\(e.g. cython\\) before trying to run setup.py.\r\n\r\nIt also adds the flags needed to statically link FFTW with clang on Mac.", "links": {"decline": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/pullrequests/53/decline"}, "diffstat": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/dedalus-project/dedalus/diffstat/dedalus-project/dedalus:ff0b5b849cd2%0D4f60496aaeac?from_pullrequest_id=53"}, "commits": {"href": "data/reposit